  "prompt": "What does worm meat taste like?",
  "response": "Worm meat, specifically referring to edible worms like mealworms or other types commonly consumed in certain cuisines, generally has a mild, nutty flavor. The texture can be crunchy, especially when they are dried or roasted, making them popular as a snack or ingredient in various dishes. In some cultures, they are used in protein bars, snacks, or included in traditional meals. The taste can vary depending on how they are prepared\u2014seasoning and cooking methods can significantly influence their flavor profile.",
